It looks to me like your issue is in the playAudio function. You are iterating over all of the subtitles at once, and setting timeouts for each one. You are overriding the previous timeout&#39;s ID when you set the next one. So the only timeout truly being canceled when you hit pause is the last one.

What you need to do is store an array of these timeout IDs. Push to the array when you make a new timeout. When you press pause, clear all timeouts from that array.

    var allTimeouts = [];
    ...
    allTimeouts.push(timeout); // On setting the timeouts
    ...
    for(int i = 0; i &lt; allTimeouts.length; i++){ // On clearing the timeouts 
        clearTimeout(allTimesouts[i]);
    }

